h3. Notes
I have reviewed all the information and reviewed the latest source code with the team:
{code}
private void updatePeopleCalendarSummary(VEvent eventComponent) {
    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
    List<Attendee> attendees = eventComponent.getProperties(Property.ATTENDEE);

    if (!(attendees == null || attendees.isEmpty())) {
        Property summary = eventComponent.getProperty(Property.SUMMARY);
        Property description = eventComponent.getProperty(Property.DESCRIPTION);

        String descriptionValue = description.getValue(); <-- NullPointerException happens here
        String newSummary = summary.getValue();

        try {
            if (isNotBlank(descriptionValue)) {
                newSummary += ": " + descriptionValue;
                summary.setValue(newSummary);
            }
        } catch (Exception e) {
            LOG.error("Error exporting to iCal", e);
        }
    }
}
{code}
h3. Workaround
 Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available
